    <bioghist>Member of Co. E, 416th Railroad Telegraph Battalion Signal Corps during World War I; later student at the University of Michigan.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Brief reminiscence of wartime activities, especially the building of telephone and telegraph lines in France; brief diary (1918-1919); memorabilia, and photographs. Also an affidavit 1890) of George W. Squier of Vermontville, Mich., regarding the death of his brother Cornelius H. Squier in 1850, on the road to California at Fort Laramie; and documents by Ray Anderson describing the circumstances of the photograph in the collection, of Paul Goebel and Fielding H. Yost at the Ann Arbor railway station.</scopecontent>
